  "prompt": "Who was the Guru of Guru Nanak Dev Ji?",
  "response": "Guru Nanak Dev Ji, the founder of Sikhism and the first of the ten Sikh Gurus, is believed to have been divinely inspired and guided by God Himself rather than having a human guru. His teachings and wisdom are considered to have come directly from his profound spiritual experiences and his connection with the Divine. In Sikh tradition, Guru Nanak Dev Ji is often referred to as **\"Satguru,\"** meaning the true Guru, and is regarded as a messenger of God. \n\nWhile he did not have a human guru, Guru Nanak Dev Ji interacted with many spiritual teachers, saints, and scholars of his time, engaging in dialogues that shaped his understanding and message of universal love, equality, and devotion to one God. His teachings emphasize the importance of **\"Waheguru\" (the Supreme Being)** as the ultimate guide and source of wisdom.",
